<div class="ClassDoc YAMLDoc" id="log" markdown="1">

# class __log__

The `log` provides data logging.

__Example__:

{% highlight python %}
# Write one line of text
log.write(u'My custom log message')
# Write all variables
log.write_vars()
{% endhighlight %}

__Overview:__


- [function __log\.\_\_init\_\___\(experiment, path\)](#function-__log__init____experiment-path)
- [function __log\.close__\(\)](#function-__logclose__)
- [function __log\.open__\(path\)](#function-__logopen__path)
- [function __log\.write__\(msg, newline=True\)](#function-__logwrite__msg-newlinetrue)
- [function __log\.write\_vars__\(var\_list=None\)](#function-__logwrite_vars__var_listnone)



<div class="FunctionDoc YAMLDoc" id="log-__init__" markdown="1">

## [function __log\.\_\_init\_\___\(experiment, path\)](#function-__log__init____experiment-path) {#function-__log__init____experiment-path}

Constructor to create a new `log` object. You do not generally call this constructor directly, because a `log` object is created automatically when the experiment is launched.

__Arguments:__

- `path` -- No description
- `experiment` -- The experiment object.
	- Type: experiment

</div>

